                      "ep_id": 5746,
                      "icon_url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/06/07/237301566/64317f914ba1543a7b2a134b9fbd63ec_4182040849691645250.png",
                      "menu_id": 10,
                      "name": "Клотар",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 7484,
                      "icon_url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2025/02/14/237301566/0de0f341fb6d635a244abdc184e5ebb7_2628006191654495454.png",
                      "menu_id": 10,
                      "name": "Ведрфёльнир",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 4910,
                      "icon_url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/01/03/237301566/59da6a8cbcffa112e5d2b63788d7051e_1480677671668697202.png",
                      "menu_id": 10,
                      "name": "Руккхадевата",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 7471,
                      "icon_url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2025/02/14/237301566/f29490bddc56b4a6773b6c5003bbb853_5720892549912855010.png",
                      "menu_id": 10,
                      "name": "Буер",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 3634,
                      "icon_url": "https://upload-static.hoyoverse.com/hoyolab-wiki/2023/03/25/134987311/413d2f1e28cddcaa782072ef8d8cbbb0_6778105082447781699.png",
                      "menu_id": 9,
                      "name": "Запретное безымянное лекарство королевского двора",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 255, 255)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Loom of Fate",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "level": 1,
                  "type": "heading"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "The Loom of Fate was extreme sorrow and pain, hope and regret coursing through one's veins, and a degree of Abyssal power that defied comprehension. Chlothar believed that once Caribert possessed all those elements, he would become the Loom of Fate. Caribert was not destined to survive, and even with the power of the \"Sinner,\" he died when he was 8 years old. He did not become the Loom of Fate himself but was used to create it. Clothar became the founder of the Abyss Order, which continued to try to create a mechanism to",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "left",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2025/04/02/237301566/6a7e4250a4a90ed5eb2cc64c7370ce0e_2474409436837992379.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Five hundred years after the Cataclysm, in Vimara Village in Sumeru, the villagers reported a young man missing. Although many people contacted the Adventurers’ Guild about the disappearance, no one could remember his name or where he lived. One of the villagers who was looking for the boy was a girl named Atossa. Together with the boy, they often came to a place near the village and talked, sitting under a tree. Sometimes, they would look at the clouds in the sky or stop to feel the wind against their skin, and they could sit there for hours at a time, never realizing how long it had been. The boy was caring, honest, and patient as he always listened to Atossa with interest as if her concerns worried him as much as her. He almost never talked about his life, only talking about unusual places, and when asked about his parents, he answered that they were no longer with him.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "right",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2025/04/02/237301566/d9051a85115256fa25ff65201cd214be_6902145588014555959.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "The Adventurers’ Guild sent its best member, the Traveler, to investigate the disappearance in the village. There, they met an old friend, the former captain of the Royal Khaenri’ahn Guard and the younger brother of the \"Sinner,\" Dainsleif, cursed with immortality. He was attracted by the strange activity of the monsters near the village, which could be related to the actions of the Abyss Order and the Loom of Fate. The activities of the Abyss Order were always accompanied by interference in the Ley Lines, which attracted monsters. When the Traveler realized that the mysterious boy only existed in the memories of people connected to the Ley Lines, together with Dainsleif, they decided to continue the investigation.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "During the investigation, Dainsleif suddenly began to have memories of the missing boy that he had not had before. Realizing that the boy was able to \"implant\" memories into people's minds and that the memories of him in Vimara Village were fake, Dainsleif and the Traveler separated. Going to the tree where the boy met with Atossa and where their carved figurine was located, the Traveler heard a mysterious voice:",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "\"...You see? We're both still here.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "We've reclaimed an endless amount of time to love.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "Release your tears. You no longer need to hold back your sorrow.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "...In the end, he whispered softly,",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "'Sleep well, Father. Sleep well, my beloved people.’",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "‘When you awake, that which differentiates us shall be no more.'\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "right",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2025/04/03/237301566/3fa574e65ddbbde772a994afbfabc912_6717333747927865823.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Following the voice, the Traveler found themselves in a subspace created by the consciousness of a missing boy. It turned out that this boy was Caribert. When the Abyss Order had not yet finished creating the Loom of Fate, the consciousness of the dead boy lingered in the mechanism, and he gained the ability to control the device until it was completed. He was not privy to the Order's plans regarding the Loom of Fate and did not see the whole picture, but the device helped him achieve his own goal. Five hundred years ago, when Clothar used the power of the Abyss to awaken the consciousness in the Hilichurl that his son became, Caribert experienced indescribable horror and pain. To console him, his father told him a story, and it allayed Caribert's fears for a moment, so he used the incomplete Loom of Fate to implant a false memory of love into the Hilichurls' minds and calm them down. Caribert also used the Loom of Fate to \"live\" a life that was unjustly taken away. He created his appearance in the image of his father and implanted the memories of the time spent with them in Vimara Village. When the project of the Abyss Order was almost completed, only a thin thread of consciousness remained from Caribert, so he decided to leave the villagers. In the end, he met with the Traveler in the space of his consciousness, where he spoke about the completion of the creation of the Loom of Fate and disappeared without a trace, allowing the Traveler to meet with their sibling. In the memories of the villagers, a memory appeared of the missing boy meeting with his parents and leaving with them.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 215, 128)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Related Entries:",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
